---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';

const updated = '2026-04-22';
---

<Base title="Terms of use — hookd" description="Terms that govern use of opskernel.io.">
  <main id="main" class="w-full px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-section">
    <article class="max-w-prose mx-auto space-y-6 text-ink">
      <header class="space-y-2">
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-muted tracking-wide">hookd · from OpsKern</p>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl tracking-tight">Terms of use</h1>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-subtle">
          Last updated {updated}
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Scope</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          These terms cover the opskernel.io website. The hookd software is governed by its own
          license terms — Apache 2.0 for the desktop edition, BSL 1.1 for the team server, custom
          for enterprise. See the
          <a class="text-accent underline" href="https://github.com/OpsKern/hookd"
            >source repository</a
          >
          for the canonical license.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">No warranty on pre-release content</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          hookd is pre-release. Copy on this site describes intended behaviour of the software.
          Actual behaviour is governed by what the software does when you run it, not by what this
          site says about it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Acceptable use</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          Don't try to break into the server, scrape the waitlist, or impersonate other visitors. We
          log enough to identify abuse and will block IPs that do.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-muted">
          hookd is operated by Will Smith (pending LLC formation) —
          <a class="text-accent underline" href="mailto:hello@opskernel.io">hello@opskernel.io</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-subtle tracking-wide pt-6">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-accent">← hookd home</a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>
